summary: SummaryNARS Afterglow Liquid Blush is a lightweight, buildable liquid blush with lasting radiance and all-day hydration. Create a lasting, natural-looking glow with a buildable, transfer-resistant formula that layers and blends without streaking.
details: DetailsBenefitsBuildable formula layers without streaking for cheek color ranging from a natural rush to intensified impact.Lightweight, ultra-creamy texture easily blends for transfer-resistant color and a lasting, natural-looking glow.Infused with skincare benefits for hydration and smooth, healthier-looking skin.Natural luminous finish.All-day hydration.Lasting color.Transfer-resistant.Buildable.Doe foot applicator.Key IngredientsSODIUM HYALURONATE: Deeply nourishes the skin barrier and provides hydration.VITAMIN E: Supports and helps defend skin against environmental aggressors with powerful antioxidant properties.PLANT PROTEIN: Promotes the appearance of smooth, plump, and healthy-looking skin.Formulated WithoutParabensTalcAlcoholPhthalatesMineral OilSulfates (SLS & SLES)Animal-derived ingredientsItem 2617037How To UseFor a second-skin wash of color, use applicator to deposit on back of hand. Use fingers to gently tap one coat onto cheeks.For a natural effect, gently tap a second coat of color on cheeks.For a bold rush, use applicator to apply two dots directly on cheeks and blend with fingers.Layer and build to desired color intensity.Sweep on powder Blush shade of choice on top to enhance the impact.IngredientsWater/Aqua/Eau, Dimethicone, PEG-10 Dimethicone, Triethylhexanoin, Butylene Glycol, Isododecane, Phenyl Trimethicone, Disteardimonium Hectorite, Trimethylsiloxysilicate, PEG-30 Dipolyhydroxystearate, Propylene Carbonate, Lauryl PEG-9 Polydimethylsiloxyethyl Dimethicone, Tocopherol, Caprylyl Glycol, Tocopheryl Acetate, Triethoxycaprylylsilane, Polyhydroxystearic Acid, Triethoxysilylethyl Polydimethylsiloxyethyl Dimethicone, Isopropyl Titanium Triisostearate, Silica, Galactoarabinan, Glycerin, Glyceryl Polyacrylate, Sodium Hyaluronate, Cocoyl Hydrolyzed Collagen, Mica, Hydrogenated Lecithin, Phenoxyethanol. May Contain: Iron Oxides (CI 77491, CI 77492, CI 77499), Red 6 Lake (CI 15850), Blue 1 Lake (CI 42090), Red 7 Lake (CI 15850), Titanium Dioxide (CI 77891).Shipping & Coupon RestrictionsThis brand is excluded from most Ulta Beauty coupons.See brand eligibility details

reviews.headline: blends great
reviews.comments: I bought (2) during Ulta's days of beauty. Behave is a blush pink great for work / every day wear. Secret lover is a lovely addition to my summer makeup routine, gives my cheeks a pop of color. Blends great with my morphe brush

reviews.headline: I would buy this product again
reviews.comments: This blush is actually really good and the color is gorgeous, but it is a pretty thin liquid.

reviews.headline: beautiful
reviews.comments: I have always loved the shade Orgasm on my fair skin and freckles. The liquid version is even better because it is so blendible and buildable.

reviews.headline: Excellent product, terrible container
reviews.comments:
I havent stopped raving about this product since buying it a few months ago but my only problem with it is the container, which is so awful I feel it deserves to lose 2 stars :(
I have always stored this blush upright and it never tips over with the way my makeup box is structured, but somehow the product seeps out into the top of the applicator and its just so messy. I have resorted to picking ip product from the screw-like pieces when using to keep it from getting unbearably messy. 
Otherwise, the color and sheen are percect for my preferences and skin tone (I'm very fair skinned with cool undertones). Product is buildable so I can tailor my look super easily. 
Also works nicely with my fingers, a brush (my preferred method), or sponge. 

Nars: PLEASE fix the stopper or whatever is causing this issue. I beg of you!

reviews.headline: wouldnt rebuy
reviews.comments: I liked the original nars blush that came with the pump. I feel it was better pigmented and I feel that with the newer bottle you do not get as much product as before. I will not buy again.

reviews.headline: sheer
reviews.comments: Im neutral with this blush. I have the color orgasm and like the peachy pink color. It is sheer and you can build it up a little bit. I like it because its natural and gives my face a little color.  I found it easy to blend with a brush but I felt like it didnt last long. I usually pair this with another cream blush or set it with a little powder blush. While its nice I don't think its worth the price when there are so many other options out there.

reviews.headline: I'm loving this color ❤️
reviews.comments: Great color for my skin type and easy to use and super pigmented and super soft application.

reviews.headline: Love this!!
reviews.comments: I have this in 3 different shades & it's amazing!!    The colors are gorgeous, it blends like a dream, and it really wears all day!!    I'm over 50 so I switched from powder blush a few years ago but never really found anything I was happy with - until this!!   It may seem pricey but a little goes a long way - and it really lasts ALL day…I'm talking about through a 10-12 hour shift and it still looks great.

reviews.headline: Lasting
reviews.comments: I bought the Orgasm color. I've received so many compliments! It doesnt fade as quick as some other high end brands.

reviews.headline: Love this blush
reviews.comments: So easy to apply. Im trying to wear make up beyond a tinted foundation at 40 and am loving this blush!

reviews.headline: Beautiful glow
reviews.comments: Very blendable and easy to use. The color orgasm rush was really pretty and had a shimmer and glow to it. If you're having a day when you want to skip bronzer and highlighter this is good for that. A little goes a long way.

reviews.headline: Blends very very easily - Aragon
reviews.comments: I bought this in the color Aragon and it's described as a warm chestnut brown but it's definitely more red than brown. At first when I applied it was really dark but blended out to almost nothing. After using it a few more times I did enjoy the light flush that it gives the cheeks but it doesn't justify the price, good thing I got this during their sale. The packaging is very shiny and chic.

reviews.headline: Ii love this product
reviews.comments: This is the blush I've been looking for.  I'm on my second tube and LOVE it.

reviews.headline: Feels like water
reviews.comments: This is a beautiful product for anyone looking for the most MINIMAL color to the cheeks. It feels like you are putting water on your face. It blended out to the lightest wash of color with the most beautiful glow. The glow can even been seen under powder. I am someone who wants a pop of color. I'm not a subtle blush gal, so this does not fit my preference. At the end of the day it is still a beautiful product, but I can't justify the price point personally. I bought this during 21 days. I got the Lilac shade.

reviews.headline: REALLY good!
reviews.comments: I'm fair with dark brown hair (same complexion and contrast as Anne Hathaway) . Dolce Vita is the most perfect blush color i've ever used. This blush blends like a dream and lasts all day. Best blush I've ever used!

reviews.headline: Beautiful color and glow
reviews.comments: This was my favorite puchase from the recent Ulta sale. It leaves a beautiful wash of color and glow, perfect for summer!

reviews.headline: Beautiful colors
reviews.comments: First time using liquid blush and WOW! Couldn't be more impressed. It blends easily over all my different foundations and the colors are very pigmented. I wish I would've purchase more colors during the sale.

reviews.headline: Fades Quickly
reviews.comments: I'm ordinarily a huge Nars fan but I was disappointed in this product. I ordered 2 colors during the sale, neither of which had any longevity. I love the colors and they blend into the skin nicely but have to be built up to achieve much color. I find many liquid blushes to be over pigmented so I don't mind that they are buildable but within an hour or two after applying they have literally disappeared. I would truly love these if I could get them to be more long lasting. They do deserve points for the soft glow they produce and a great color selection. I have very dry skin so perhaps my skin quickly absorbs this formula but they were a bit of a miss for me for that reason.

reviews.headline: Blendable and beautiful
reviews.comments: I was shocked at how much i love this. It is so much more user friendly than the Rare blushes. Highly recommend.

reviews.headline: Thus is fabulous liquid blush!
reviews.comments: This is the first time I use a liquid blush and I love it! It makes your skin glow. I also use a small amount to make it look more natural. I will definitely buy again.

media.headline: Beautiful Blush
media.caption:
I received this NARS Cosmetics Afterglow Liquid Blush in Behave from BzzAgent in exchange for my honest review. This is a mauve pink shade that is perfect for light complexion skin. It's lightweight and buildable.    Apply a couple dots on your cheek and blend. Keep applying until you reach your desired pigment. This blush has a natural looking glow and its transfer resistant. It's infused with skincare benefits for 8-hour hydration and smooth, healthier skin. The key ingredients are Hyaluronic Acid, Vitamin E and Vegan Collagen. I absolutely love this blush and I will use this daily. I can't wait to get more shades of this blush. I highly recommend this product!

faceoff_positive.comments: I recently had the opportunity to try out the NARS Afterglow Liquid Blush in the shade Behave, courtesy of BzzAgent. Let me tell you, I am absolutely thrilled with this product!    Behave is a stunning warm pink coral hue that effortlessly adds a natural and luminous flush to my cheeks. The formula itself is exceptionally lightweight, making its application a breeze and allowing for customizable coverage. Its seamless blending capabilities result in a gorgeous satin finish that enhances my skin's appearance.    One of the standout features of this blush is its remarkable longevity. Even after a full day of wear, the color remains vivid and fresh, refusing to fade or become patchy. It truly works wonders in achieving a healthy and youthful glow that lasts.    All in all, I am overjoyed with the NARS Afterglow Liquid Blush in the shade Behave. It has quickly become an essential part of my makeup routine, and I wholeheartedly recommend it to anyone in search of a top-notch blush that delivers a natural and enduring radiance. Many thanks to BzzAgent for the opportunity to discover this absolute gem!
faceoff_positive.headline: Behave is a Stunning shade

faceoff_negative.comments: I've always loved Nars as a brand but their recent launches are out of touch and have missed the mark. The concept of this blush is great but the execution is severely lacking. I do love the texture of the blush, it's like a water gel. Went on easily however it's very sheer. The color I received free for my review was Lilac, a shade I would never in a million years choose for myself. It faded rather quickly but for the price I wouldn't buy or recommend this blush. Too many better less expensive options out there. I really do love Nars and wish they step it up! The packaging also feels kind of cheap.
faceoff_negative.headline: Wouldn't repurchase
